cluster_relations.rel_desc: Birds contribute to the ecological process of seed dispersal.
Birds contribute to pollination as an ecological process.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject exerts a positive causal or functional influence on the state, process, or property represented by the object, without implying sole responsibility or strict determinism.
args.justification: All three relations describe the subject providing a positive causal or functional contribution to a broader ecological state or process (biodiversity, seed dispersal, pollination). The direction and semantics match a generic 'contributes_to' predicate, so they can be normalized under a single canonical relation.

Each relation captures how a biotic component or its status (plant species, birds) contributes to an ecosystem function, process, or state (biodiversity, seed dispersal, pollination). Grouping them under an 'ecosystem_function_contribution_relation' class reflects this common ecological-function contribution pattern.

The relations express that the subject has a causal or enabling effect on the object (e.g., birds enabling seed dispersal and pollination, plant species status affecting biodiversity), which fits a causal influence dimension better than purely associative or compositional categories.
